response.Q0: I focused on the outer (final) nodes and didn't check the inner ones as the value of the outer nodes was more important to the final total than the value of the nodes on the path towards it.
response.Q1: Only after the first couple of games when i realised it was better to work backwards and select an outer node to travel to.
response.Q2: It was always weighing up whether to continue towards a mid-value node or to spend more money trying to discover a higher value one. I'm not sure my performance improved past the first few games as I'd settled on a strategy then.
